unjab Women Commission, one of the cases of 2018 was reopened. In that case, Charanjit Singh Channi was blamed for sending inappropriate messages to an IAS officer Kavita Singh. Family Charanjit Singh Channi married Dr Kamaljit Singh. The duo has two sons, Navjit Singh (who did his law degree from PEC University) and Rhythmjit Singh. Channi's father, Mr Harsa Singh elected for the Sarpanch when Channi didn't even start his political career. His mother, late Ajmer Kaur, was a housewife. He has siblings named Manmohan Singh (retired chief engineer), Dr Manohar Singh (specialist in medical for Punjab government), Sukhwant Singh (a budding leader), and one of his sisters named Surinder Kaur. Facts about Charanjit Singh Channi On 20th September 2021, Charanjit Singh Channi was appointed as the Chief Minister of Punjab. Channi was Punjab's 1st Dalit Sikh Chief Minister. Charanjit Singh Channi became the sixteenth Chief Minister of Punjab and took the pledge in Raj Bhavan, Chandigarh, on September 20, 2021. He arrived on a motorbike driven by previous Punjab Pradesh Congress Committee chairman Sunil Jakhar to take the commitment at Raj Bhavan at Chandigarh. He attended a local government school in his town for his primary level education. His father belonged to a low-income family in Punjab. Later his father went to Malaysia for better earnings and good life. He worked hard in Malaysia and returned to India after his good and wealthy personality. In India, he started his tent house business which he ran. Charanjit Singh Channi, in his childhood, helped his father in the business. Later, his father became the Sarpanch in the native village and a member of Samiti. Charanjit Singh Channi is outstanding in handball games and bhangra. At Punjab University, he represented his university in handball and won a gold medal in the Inter-University Sports meet. He further took part in National Scheme Services, National Cadet Corps, debating, as well as other cultural activities at the university. He was also selected for student union leader when he studied in class 10th in Khalsa Senior Secondary School, Kharar. He got 472 votes out of 1000 votes in his school. He also won the election, which was held for general secretory in Shri Guru Gobind Singh College, when he was doing his graduation. He is well-known for his academic qualifications, which include a master's degree in politics as well as an MBA degree. He once said in the media that he wanted to be excellent in his studies. He said he got inspired by his brother Manmohan Singh. He further said his brother got his degree while working in a government office. Channi's career in politics began in 2002 when he had been chosen for the fourteenth Punjab Vidhan Sabha's opposition party. For two years, he presided over Kharar's Municipal Council. Later, he worked on Committee on Subordinate Legislation, Privileges Committee, and for Punjab Vidhan Sabha. Channi defeated a congressperson in the Chamkaur Sahib District poll, and he won that election on his own. After his victory, he spoke with Shiromani Akali Dal and then was elected as an associate person of the legislature. Captain Amrinder Singh returned Channi towards the Indian National Congress on December 2010. Harish Rawat (Senior of the Congress) announced on Twitter that Charanjit Singh Channi had been appointed as Punjab's sixteenth Chief Minister. Charanjit Singh Channi once said that he loves to travel a lot, and his favourite places to travel include Singapore, England, Dubai, and South Korea. Channi performed the bhangra during an occasion in Kapurthala, Punjab, just a few days after being appointed as Chief Minister of Punjab. A clip of the newly appointed Chief Minister showing his dance steps on a podium with a folk performer became popular on social media. Channi attempted to establish positive connections with Rahul Gandhi with the support of CP Joshi, a senior congress member, after joining the Indian National Congress in 2010. 